# Product Requirement Document (PRD)

## Introduction

This document defines the product requirements for the MediGo Medicine Delivery System. It outlines the features, goals, user needs, and expected behavior of the system.

---

## Product Goal

To build a mobile-based medicine delivery platform that allows users to order medicines online, upload prescriptions, and receive medicines at their doorstep efficiently and securely.

---

## Product Scope

The system will include:

* Mobile application for users
* Web-based admin dashboard
* Backend API for managing data and orders

The system will not initially include:

* Real-time doctor consultation
* Hospital integration

---

## Key Features

### 1. User Features

* User registration and login
* Medicine search and browsing
* Add to cart and checkout
* Prescription upload
* Order tracking
* Order history

---

### 2. Admin Features

* Manage medicines and inventory
* Approve or reject prescription orders
* Manage user orders
* View reports and analytics

---

### 3. System Features

* Secure authentication system
* Real-time database updates
* Notification system for order updates

---

## User Requirements

Users should be able to:

* Easily find medicines
* Place orders without difficulty
* Upload prescriptions safely
* Track delivery status

---

## Constraints

* Internet connection required
* Prescription validation depends on admin/pharmacy
* Delivery time depends on logistics system

---

## Assumptions

* Users have smartphones
* Pharmacies are willing to participate in the system
* Users understand basic mobile app usage

---

## Success Criteria

The product will be considered successful if:

* Users can place medicine orders successfully
* Admin can manage orders efficiently
* System works smoothly without major errors
